<HEADLINE> Yugoslavia To Ask Extradition of Concentration Camp Operator </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, April 16 (Xinhua) - The Yugoslav government has
decided to submit a request for the extradition from Argentina of
a Croat who ran a World War II concentration camp in Croatia, the
Tanjug news agency reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The suspect, Dinko Sakic, has been living in Argentina since
1947.
</P>
<P>
Tens of thousands of people were killed at the Jasenovac camp
in World War II. 
</P>
</TEXT>
