<HEADLINE> S.Lankan PM Meets Chinese Amity Delegation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, April 16 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan Prime Minister
Sirimavo Bandaranaike Thursday met with a delegation from the
Chinese People's Association for Friendship with Foreign Countries
(CPAFFC) led by Su Guang, its vice-president.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, they had a friendly conversation about
Sino-Sri Lankan relations, sources close to the meeting said.
</P>
<P>
They expressed satisfaction over the growing friendly ties
between the two countries, and hoped that the friendship and
cooperation would be further expanded.
</P>
<P>
The delegation arrived in Colombo on Sunday for a six-day
good-will visit to Sri Lanka.
</P>
<P>
During its stay here, the delegation also met Minister of
Tourism and Civil Aviation Dharmasiri Senanayake.
</P>
<P>
The delegation will leave for home on Friday. 
</P>
