<HEADLINE> Wanda Back In Top Spot of Chinese Soccer League </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 16 (Xinhua) -- Defending champions Dalian Wanda
paced their way in the Chinese football first division league
after Thursday's 4-1 cushion of Shenzhen Pingan in Dalian,
Liaoning Province, while Chinese Army thrashed Guangzhou Songri
3-0 at home in Chongqing.
</P>
<P>
Thursday's matches were the third round ties which were
postponed because Wanda played in the Asian Club Champions final,
and Chinese Army played an international tournament in Singapore.
</P>
<P>
Wanda began to extend their lead in the overall standings to
three points from four wins and one draw over second Qingdao
Hainiu, while Chinese Army moved onto the mid-table after
Thursday's victory.
</P>
<P>
Nigerian striker Tomou Berfin Bayard scored the sole goal in
the 53rd minute for Pingan, which is the only one conceded by the
title-holders so far this season.
</P>
<P>
Wang Tao found the net twice in the second half of the one-side
match. Wanda had almost secured the victory on two first-half
goals from Hans Eklund and Hao Haidong.
</P>
<P>
Wanda coach Xu Genbao, who took the pole at the start of the
season after left Shenzhen Pingan, which finished fourth last
season in the second division, said his club began their campaine
of winning the title for the third consecutive time after the win.
</P>
<P>
Hu Yunfeng scored once and created another, but Chinese Army
played apparently a better defence than their attack in their
first home victory this season.
</P>
<P>
Wang Lei opened the mark seconds before the half-time on a
right flank cross from Hu, who extended the lead to 2-0 in the
70th minute.
</P>
<P>
Tao Pei sealed the match with a sole run in the 88th minute,
but his teammates squadered a dozen of gold opportunities to
change the mark. 
</P>
</TEXT>
