<HEADLINE> German Car Industry Reports New Dynamic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, April 16 (Xinhua) -- After a slow start at the beginning
of 1998, German car production and orders are regaining momentum
in March, the German Automotive Industry Association VDA said.
</P>
<P>
According the VDA, German carmakers turned out 517,600 vehicles
in March, up 21 percent from a year ago.
</P>
<P>
While foreign orders for German cars maintained at the high
levels of the previous months, domestic orders picked up strongly
by 12 percent in March after a relatively flat period at the
beginning this year, the VDA said.
</P>
<P>
For the first quarter as a whole, German carmakers turned out a
total of 1.35 million vehicles, a growth of eight percent over the
same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, German car exports also grew by six percent to
804,400 in the first three months, including 320,100 exported in
March alone. 
</P>
</TEXT>
