<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Egypt-Syria Summit Promotes Arab Solidarity: AL </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, April 16 (Xinhua) -- Arab League Secretary General Ahmed
Esmat Abdel-Meguid said on Thursday that the latest Egypt-Syria
summit has promoted the Arab solidarity.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to the Middle East News Agency, Abdel-Meguid termed
the summit as "a strong phenomenon" further deepening inter-Arab
relations for the good of the Arab nation.
</P>
<P>
"The meeting mirrored the Arab unity in support of the Lebanese
and Syrian stances and the sustained rejection of Israeli attempts
to empty U.N. Security Council Resolution 425 from its kernel," he
said.
</P>
<P>
Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak and his Syrian counterpart
Hafez al-Assad held talks here on Wednesday on Israeli proposal of
a conditional withdrawal from south Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders stressed that the withdrawal should be
unconditional. Mubarak assured al-Assad that Egypt sides with
Syria and Lebanon on this issue.
</P>
<P>
Israel decided on April 1 to endorse the United Nations Security
Council Resolution 425, which calls for a unilateral Israeli
withdrawal from Lebanon. But meanwhile, it said that no troop
pullback would be conducted unless security arrangements are
reached with the Lebanese government.
</P>
<P>
Both Lebanon and Syria, which agree not to make peace
separately with Israel, have rejected Israel's offer.
</P>
<P>
Syria has been seeking the return of the Golan Heights, which
Israel captured from Syria in the 1967 Mideast War.
</P>
<P>
The summit further underscored the importance of honoring
agreements the previous Israeli government agreed upon,
Abdel-Meguid said.
</P>
<P>
"The Arab nation's choice of peace as a strategic option and
objective does not mean that it gives up the Arab rights. But
rather this choice came to prove that it is bent on achieving a
just and comprehensive peace in the Mideast, in accordance with
the U.N. resolutions and the land-for-peace principle," he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
