<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1600 GMT, April 16 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG -- The death toll of a horror crash near Newcastle
in South Africa's Kwazulu-Natal province has risen to 31 Thursday,
South African Press Association reported.
</P>
<P>
The dead included 23 school children. Over 50 other people were
wounded.
</P>
<P>
The disaster occurred shortly after 1300 GMT and five vehicles
were involved. Four of the vehicles, including a school bus and a
horse and trailer, fell into a 50-meter embankment.
(S. Africa-crash death)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JAKARTA -- Indonesian President Soeharto has called on the
protesting students to return to class and develop their
competitiveness in order to face the future.
</P>
<P>
Thousands of students kept up their demands for reforms and
lower prices of basic commodities Wednesday at campus rallies
organized concurrently at dozens of universities in the country.
(Indonesia-President-Students)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
CAIRO -- British Prime Minister Tony Blair has said Israel's
offer to pull back from south Lebanon would be more effective if
it is linked with a similar move on the Syrian track.
</P>
<P>
"The application will be easier if progress would be made
within the context of a comprehensive settlement mainly on the
Syrian track," he told the Arabic daily Al Ahram in an interview
published Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Israel decided on April 1 to endorse the U.N. Security Council
Resolution 425, but conditioned a pullback from south Lebanon on
making security arrangements with the Lebanese government.
(Egypt-Britain-Blair)
</P>
