BANGKOK -- The Thai military on Thursday confirmed the death of
Pol Pot, former leader of the Khmer Rouge.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Thai TV Channel Nine showed the corpse of Pol Pot
wearing a grey shirt. He was lying on a bed in a cottage in
Cambodia near the border with Thailand. (Thailand-Pol Pot-Death)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LONDON -- About three quarters of voters on both sides of the
Irish border would say "yes" to the historic Northern Ireland
peace accord in next month's referendum, an opinion poll showed on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
In Northern Ireland, 73 percent would vote for the accord,
while in the rest of Britain, 81 percent would back the peace
deal. In the Republic of Ireland, 61 percent of voters would show
their favor if they were asked to vote. (Britain-N.Irish
Accord-Poll)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
