<P>
BEIRUT -- An Israeli-allied South Lebanese Army (SLA) member
was killed in a roadside bomb explosion in south Lebanon Thursday
morning, Lebanese Voice of the People reported.
</P>
<P>
This is the second bomb blast in less than two days. Two
Israeli soldiers were wounded in another roadside bomb explosion
on Wednesday, which was donated by the Iranian-backed Hezbollah,
or Party of God. (Lebanon-SLA-Killed) 
</P>
