<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe to Increase Telephone Charges </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, April 16 (Xinhua) --The Zimbabawe Posts and
Telecommunication has announced it will charge more national and
international telephone fees by 10 and 20 percent from this
Friday.
</P>
<P>
Southern African Broadcasting Association Thursday quoted sources
from the Zimbabwean corporation as saying that the corporation will
also reduce costs on calls made out of peak hours.
</P>
<P>
Tony Marechera, the corporation's Deputy Postmaster-General,
said calls will go up by 12 percent from 37 Zimbabwean cents to
50 cents (One U.S. dollar equals 3.16 Zimbabwean Dollars) for
three minutes.
</P>
<P>
International traffic, which contribute 60 percent of the
corporation's tatal revenue, has been adversely affected by loss
of value of the Zimbabwe Dollar.
</P>
<P>
Marechera said his corporation needs to generate more funds to
expand and improve telepone services in the country. 
</P>
