<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 16 (Xinhua) -- U.S. Treasury Secretary Robert
Rubin warned Thursday that Asia's full recovery from the financial
turmoil cannot be achieved unless Japan does more to pull its
economy from recession.
</P>
<P>
"Despite the welcome signs of stability now emerging (in Asia)
... we must guard against complacency," he told the Interim
Committee of the International Monetary Fund (IMF).
</P>
