one-day session, focusing on the financial crisis in Asia and
Japan's economic problems.
</P>
<P>
Japan, the world's second largest economy, accounts for more
than half of Asia's output, he said.
</P>
<P>
Rubin said that Japan "must generate substantial growth to help
maintain a growing world economy and to absorb a growing share of
imports from emerging markets." 
