and territorial integrity of the Comoros and address the genuine
socio-economic and institutional problems of all the islands.
</P>
<P>
It was observed that consultations were going-on on the
measures to be taken to put an end to the crisis within the
context of the mission report of the ministerial delegation to
the Comoros, the press release added.
</P>
<P>
Anjouan and Moheli, which along with Grand Comore won
statehood from France as the Federal Islamic Republic of the
Comoros in 1975, broke away a year ago complaining of neglect by
the central government.
</P>
<P>
Anjouan secessionists said they would still reject any OAU
effort to reintegrate Anjouan with Grand Comore and help Moroni
authorities "reduce our people to slaves."
