<HEADLINE> Romanian Capital Markets Record Meager Increases </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, April 16 (Xinhua) -- The increase of the Romanian
capital market in the first quarter of this year was a meager 5,3
percent, compared with the 93,2 percent increase recorded for the
same period of the last year when the country being considered one
of the most performing of the Eastern European emerging markets.
</P>
<P>
The overall performance of the Romanian economy triggered a
reserved attitude of the foreign investors, which could not be
compensated by domestic economics, financial analysts argue.
</P>
<P>
According to the local securities officials, a reorienting of
interests was evident at industrial sector level, The rising
sectors of the previous year - cement, building materials, oil and
energy, metals and steel, were superseded by electronics and
electrotechnics, civil engineering and services.
</P>
<P>
Despite optimism of some brokerage companies over the relaunch
of the capital market in Romania, the Director of the General
Investment Group Vlad Vasiliu says 1998 "is yet a year of
compromise". 
</P>
