<HEADLINE> ECOMOG Chief in Control of S. Leone Internal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, April 16 (Xinhua) -- Col. Maxwell Kobe, the ECOMOG
commander in Sierra Leone, has been appointed by the Sierra
Leonean government to assume control of the country's internal
security, the British Broadcasting Corporation reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Confirming the government announcement, a presidential
spokesman said since the Sierra Leonean army has become
discredited, the government has to give the crucial job to Col.
Kobe, who will have a second person to help.
</P>
<P>
He will be responsible to President Ahmed Tejan Kabbah, the
commander-in-chief of the Sierra Leonean armed forces, the
spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
Col. Kobe led the west African peace keeping force (ECOMOG) to
drive the military junta out of the capital Freetown in
mid-February, paving the way for the reinstatement of Kabbah's
government ousted in the coup last May.
</P>
<P>
The troops under the Nigerian officer are now carrying out a
mopping up exercise to flush out the remnants of junta forces and
allied rebels in eastern Sierra Leone.
</P>
<P>
However, the spokesman denied speculations that the
appointment, announced Wednesday night, has something to do with
compensation to his contribution in the peace process.
</P>
<P>
"What he is simply doing is helping us restructure our army
and advise us of the assistance we need in the guideline of
equipment for the new Sierra Leonean army," the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
But he admitted that Col. Kobe is a very popular person whom
Sierra Leoneans are proud of and fond of, adding that "I believe
he will do a wonderful job for us."
</P>
<P>
As for the situation in the eastern diamond-rich areas of the
tiny west African country, where the junta forces and allied
rebels take as their last strongholds, the spokesman said with
the "very certificate ECOMOG presence there", the whole situation
will be resolved shortly.
</P>
<P>
The only two districts which remain under the control of the
junta force will shortly be liberated, he said, adding that the
government will not abandon the ordinary people there.
</P>
<P>
What the government is doing is for the interest of the
country to ensure that the whole country is to be liberated, the
spokesman said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
