Administration in this regard has proved fruitless so far.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, other 15 opposition parties including the National
Movement of Mozambique also announced that they would not
participate in the elections, citing lack of funds for
inspections over the election process.
</P>
<P>
Nonetheless, Manuel Tome, general secretary of the Mozambique
Liberation Front party, stressed Thursday that the elections will
take place even if there is only one party, his party, which has
registered. 
