commission to investigate the immediate causes of the incidents.
</P>
<P>
The trouble in the east started from April 4 when some members
of Karimojong, a Momad tribe living in the northeast of the
country, raided adjacent areas in the east where some of their
children were missing, and cattles were rustled. The raids spread
thereafter southward in the country.
</P>
<P>
The Karimojong men killed 20 people including five soldiers
and looted about a thousand cattle during last week alone, said
William Omaria, State Minister for Internal Affairs.
</P>
<P>
The government has pledged to take measures to restore order
and law in the east, to rescue abducted people, return looted
cattle to their lawful owners and compensate for the victims.
