<HEADLINE> Tianjin Tax Official Sentenced to Life Imprisonment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Luo Shuangyin, former deputy
director of the Tianjin Taxation Consultation Office, was
sentenced to life imprisonment today for embezzling public funds
totalling 623,000 yuan and accepting bribes of over 400,000 yuan.
</P>
<P>
Luo, 44, abused his power and embezzled the public funds
between December 1996 to April 1997.
</P>
<P>
In November 1996, Luo demanded 400,000 yuan from a Tianjin
company to squash a tax evasion investigation.
</P>
<P>
The Tianjin No.2 Intermediate People's Court confirmed the
illegal activities and sentenced Luo to life imprisonment, in
addition to the deprivation of political rights for life and the
confiscation of personal belongings valued at 50,000 yuan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
