<HEADLINE> HK Experience Justifies China's Policy: Macao Governor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Macao Governor Vasco Rocha Vieira
said here today that the experience in Hong Kong has justified
China's policy of "one country, two systems."
</P>
<P>
"Hong Kong's experience is a test of the 'one country, two
systems' policy for the first time," he told a reception ceremony
for visiting Portuguese Prime Minister Antonio Guterres.
</P>
<P>
"What has happened in Hong Kong since its handover means a
favorable factor to Macao. It has proved the policy has solid
basis," he said.
</P>
<P>
Vieira told Guterres and about 100 Macao officials and
celebrities that Macao's transitional affairs have been conducted
smoothly in an atmosphere of stability, cooperation, safety and
friendship.
</P>
<P>
Guterres said in his speech that he has full confidence in and
is optimistic about Macao's stability, prosperity and progress in
the future.
</P>
<P>
Both the governor and the prime minister stressed that Portugal
should take advantage of Macao and its smooth transition to
expand the friendly relations with China.
</P>
<P>
Guterres will start his China's inland visit Sunday.  
</P>
