<HEADLINE> Shanghai Stock Market Goes Down This Week </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 17 (Xinhua) -- The momentum of the Shanghai
Stock Market slowed this week compared to last, with declines in
both the stock index and turnover.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Composite Index on the Shanghai Stock Exchange
ended the week at 1,298.11, down 1.02 percent on the previous week.
</P>
<P>
The SSE-30 Index, which is based on 30 blue chip stocks
selected from more than 300 A-Share stocks available for domestic
investors, edged down 2.34 percent to close at 3,771.68.
</P>
<P>
The total transaction volume plummented 20 percent on the
previous week to end at 39.11 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
B-share stocks sold to foreign investors closed at 53.45, down
1.37 percent. The 149 million yuan in turnover throughout the week
was slightly higher than the previous week.
</P>
<P>
This week's trading volume for funds stood at 2.56 billion
yuan, down a quarter when compared to the previous week.
</P>
<P>
The bond market registered a transaction volume of 33.79
billion yuan, up 12.6 percent on last week. 
</P>
</TEXT>
