<HEADLINE> Karachi Stock Exchange Index Goes Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, April 17 (Xinhua) -- The Karachi Stock Exchange
(KSE) -100 Index went down by 8.03 points Friday to close at
1,596.13 points.
</P>
<P>
A total volume of 52 million shares traded on Friday against 46
million traded Wednesday. The KSE remained closed on Thursday due
to a religious holiday.
</P>
<P>
There were 48 gainers and 71 losers while share prices of 43
companies remained unchanged on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Brokers said Friday was a slow session and punters covered
their positions as there was little buying from foreign investors
and this discouraged local players.
</P>
<P>
Brokers expect the KSE index to drop to mid-1,500 level in the
coming week and say that there will be a rebound only on foreign
buying.
</P>
<P>
Much depends on the foreign inflows into the market as domestic
players are playing a wait-and-see game, they said.  
</P>
