<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 17 (Xinhua) -- French President Jacques Chirac
Friday promised his Montenegrin counterpart Milo Jukanovic the
full support of France in his economic reform program.
</P>
<P>
"Montenegro will have the resolute support of France," said
Chirac during a meeting with Jukanovic, who was on a three-day
visit to France.
</P>
<P>
Jukanovic expressed satisfaction over the promise by France to
provide aid to Montenegro and a French initiative of speeding up
European Union aid to Montenegro.
</P>
<P>
France will also seek to exempt Montenegro from the
international sanctions against Yugoslavia in some fields,
Jukanovic told reporters.
</P>
<P>
During the talks, Jukanovic briefed Chirac on "the axis" of his
policy, such as the adoption of a market economy, the
privatization of state-owned firms, the democratization of
political life, and the enhancement of cooperation between
Montenegro and other parts of Europe.
</P>
<P>
The Republic of Montenegro and the Republic of Serbia make up
the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
On the crisis in Kosovo, a province of Serbia, Chirac expressed
his great concern over the attitude of the Yugoslav authorities
toward the crisis.
</P>
<P>
The French president also called for a peaceful solution to the
issue through dialogue. 
</P>
