<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1430 GMT, April 17 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW -- President Boris Yeltsin on Friday officially
renominated Sergei Kiriyenko as his candidate for prime minister
for a third round vote, ITAR-TASS news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The president ordered Kremlin officials to resubmit Kiriyenko's
nomination after the State Duma refused to confirm his nomination
for the second time in a vote earlier. (Russia-PM Renomination)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- The nomination of Sergei Kiriyenko as Russian prime
minister on Friday failed to pass the second vote at the State
Duma, the lower house of Russian parliament.
</P>
<P>
The deputies voted 115 in favor, 271 against with 11
abstentions to reject the nomination by President Boris Yeltsin.
</P>
<P>
Under the country's constitution, the premier's nomination
needs 226 votes in favor from the 450-seat lower house to be
confirmed. (Russia-Duma-Kiriyenko)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ULAN BATOR -- The Mongolian government led by Prime Minister
Mendsaikhan Enkhsaikhan on Friday submitted an offer to the
president to resign en masse, paving the way for a reshuffle of
the coalition government.
</P>
<P>
The president is examing the offer, a spokesman for the
president said. (Mongolia-Cabinet Resignation)
</P>
<P>
