</P>
<P>
ISLAMABAD -- The visiting Special Envoy of U.S. President Bill
Clinton, Bill Richardson, has secured a ceasefire from the Afghan
Taliban militia, according to a report by the Associated Press of
Pakistan on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Taliban also agreed to hold talks with opposition forces by
April 27, Richardson announced in Afghanistan's capital of Kabul.
(Afghanistan-US-Taliban Ceasefire)
</P>
