<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing Reports Rising Foreign Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Beijing reported robust growth in
foreign trade for the first quarter of this year, with total
exports and imports reaching 1.34 billion US dollars, up 15.8
percent on the 1997 period.
</P>
<P>
Recent statistics released by Beijing Customs reveals that
Beijing's first quarter exports surged 25.7 percent to 640 million
US dollars.
</P>
<P>
A further breakdown shows a 160 million US dollars export
volume for the processing sector, up 32 percent on the first
quarter in 1997. The figure accounted for 37.6 percent of
Beijing's total export volume.
</P>
<P>
Statistics also show that Beijing approved 131 foreign-funded
enterprises during the period, with total contracted investment
standing at 521 million US dollars, up 7.4 percent on the 1997
period. Foreign funds actually used grew by 15 percent to 940
million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Experts noted that the figures indicate that Beijing has
basically countered negative effects that financial turmoil in
Southeast Asia has created in terms of attracting foreign
investment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
