<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing to Treat Pollution in Summer Palace Moat </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Beijing is preparing to tackle
pollution problems besetting the Summer Palace moat, according to
the the Beijing Municipal Works Management Office.
</P>
<P>
The project is part of the municipal government's three major
plans to clean the city's rivers and lakes within three years.
</P>
<P>
The 3,800-meter long and 52-meter wide moat encircles the city
walls of the Summer Palace.
</P>
<P>
The fact that the original drainage system diverts both
rainwater and wastewater into the moat has created severe
pollution problems.
</P>
<P>
The project, scheduled to begin no later than May, will focus
on restructuring the drainage system.
</P>
<P>
The project will include the construction of seven drainage
channels stretching a total of 7,500 meters. The new channels will
divert wastewater to the Gaobei Sewage Treatment Plant in east
Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Related departments will also build projects to clean
up surrounding areas.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
