<HEADLINE> Portuguese PM Confident of Macao's Future </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Portuguese Prime Minister Antonio
Guterres said here today that he has full confidence in and is
optimistic about Macao's stability, prosperity and progress in the
future.
</P>
<P>
Guterres made the remarks at a reception ceremony after his
arrival at noon for a three-day visit to Macao en route to his
official visit to China's inland areas.
</P>
<P>
"I am fully confident of and optimistic about the stability,
prosperity and progress in Macao," he said in a speech. "Portugal
and the government under my leadership will make cordial efforts."
</P>
<P>
Guterres said the time of his visit coincides with the crucial
stage in Macao's unique transition, which has been conducted in a
"harmonious manner."
</P>
<P>
He promised to Macao residents that the Portuguese Government
will "make its utmost efforts to make the historical stage wrap up
in a harmonious and stable atmosphere."
</P>
<P>
He said Macao has played an important role in the bilateral
relations between Portugal and China, and will continue to be a
crucial point of cooperation between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
"We must take use of Macao and the transition as a dynamic
element to expand the relations between Portugal and China well
beyond the cooperation in Macao," he said.
</P>
<P>
Coming along with the prime minister are dozens of businessmen
and six cabinet ministers, including Foreign Minister Jaime Gama,
Economic Affairs Minister Pina Moura and Science and Technology
Minister Mariano Gago.
</P>
<P>
During his stay here, Guterres is scheduled to meet leading
officials of the Macao Government, the bishop of Macao Diocese,
leaders of local major communities and Chinese officials based in
Macao. He will also inaugurate the Macao Museum. 
</P>
</TEXT>
