USA Today:
</P>
<P>
-- A crucial data processor failed hours before space shuttle
Columbia was to lift off Thursday, forcing a delay and the hurried
replacement of 1,514 crickets and 18 pregnant mice. Liftoff was
reset for Friday.
</P>
<P>
-- Downtown Nashville resembled a war zone after two tornadoes
blasted through Thursday afternoon, injuring at least 100. 
</P>
