<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiang Zemin On Economic Work (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Jiang Zemin, general secretary
of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC),
stressed that the country's leading task at present is to boost
economic development to ensure an 8 percent increase in this
year's gross domestic product (GDP).
</P>
<P>
Jiang, also Chinese president and chairman of the Central
Military Commission, said during an April 13-17 visit to Chongqing
Municipality that in accordance with the essence of the second
plenary session of the 15th CPC Central Committee, China will
build a socialist economy, politics and culture with Chinese
characteristics, in line with its national conditions.
</P>
<P>
"We must correctly handle relations between reforms,
development and stability," he told local officials and people.
</P>
<P>
The leader also emphasized the importance of arming the whole
Party with the Deng Xiaoping Theory and using the theory to guide
all kinds of work.
</P>
<P>
Jiang called for faster development of high-tech industries and
speeding up infrastructure construction in the sectors of
agriculture, water conservancy, transportation, telecommunications
and environmental protection.
</P>
<P>
He said, "We should expand domestic demand, explore the
domestic market, appropriately increase investment and consumption
demand, adjust the country's economic structure and improve our
economic efficiency."
</P>
<P>
He also called for efforts to expand China's existing
international market, open up a new global market, strive for a
steady increase in exports and maintain the stability of the value
of Chinese currency.
</P>
<P>
To attain this year's economic development goal, he noted, it
is imperative to push forward the restructuring of state-owned
enterprises, the reform of the financial system, and the
restructuring of government institutions.
</P>
<P>
He also asked governments at all levels to make a success of
the reform of the grain circulation system, the reform of the
urban housing system, the reform of the medical insurance system,
and the re-employment of laid-off workers.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that the restructuring of state-owned
enterprises is a major task for this year's economic work
assigned by the CPC Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
Jiang called on governments at all levels to make greater
efforts to help most of the large- and medium-size state-owned
enterprises which are running in the red to overcome difficulties
in about three years.
</P>
<P>
Accompanied by Vice-Premier Wen Jiabao and Zhang Delin,
secretary of the Chongqing Municipal CPC Committee, Jiang visited
a number of companies in automotive manufacturing, iron
and steel, ceramic and other industrial businesses in Chongqing.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980417.0129 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiang Zemin on Economic Work (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jiang pointed out that employment, as a major issue that must
be a long-term concern, requires hard work to handle well because
China has a large population.
</P>
<P>
Re-directing laid-off workers and their re-employment is
essential not only to the success of the reform of state-owned
enterprises, but also to the country's social stability, he said.
</P>
<P>
He emphasized that reducing staff and increasing efficiency
must be conducted along with re-employment, and laying off workers
and re-directing the layoffs must be taken into consideration
simultaneously.
</P>
<P>
He said the government encourages enterprises to tap their
potential to diversify their operations in order to generate more
jobs for their redundant employees, while it will vigorously
develop the service sector to provide more employment opportunities
for the laid-off workers.
</P>
<P>
"We should encourage laid-off workers to establish their own
businesses or become self-employed," he told local officials.
</P>
<P>
Referring to agriculture, the leader said the country must
strengthen the farming sector as the foundation of the national
economy, while accelerating the development of the rural economy
and solving the problem of rural poverty by and large by the end
of the century.
</P>
<P>
Basic policies on the rural areas, such as extending the period
of land contracts and lightening farmers's financial burdens, must
be carried out to the letter, he said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, he said, efforts should be made to improve farm
production conditions by accelerating construction of agricultural
infrastructure, while readjusting the rural industrial
structure in accordance with market demand.
</P>
<P>
He also called for redoubled efforts in poverty relief work,
consolidating grass-roots organizations, and promoting democracy,
the introduction of a legal system, and ethical and cultural
progress in rural areas.
</P>
<P>
Jiang fully acknowledged the sound beginning of each piece of
work since the establishment of the Chongqing municipality a year
ago, saying the decision to establish the municipality was
entirely correct.
</P>
<P>
He asked officials and people in Chongqing to emancipate
their minds and work hard to turn the municipality into a new
modern city in the not too distant future.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
