<HEADLINE> Gillette Co. Reports 13.6 Percent Profit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES, April 16 (Xinhua) -- Gillette Company Thursday
reported a 13.6-percent increase in its first-quarter profits.
</P>
<P>
Gillette said it had a net income of 268 million U.S. dollars
in the first quarter of 1998, compared with 236 million dollars a
year ago.
</P>
<P>
Sales for the first quarter of this year were 2.02 billion
dollars, up 1.5 percent over the 1.99 billion dollars registered
in the same period last year, the company added.
</P>
<P>
Alfred Zeien, chairman of Gillette, said the strong quarterly
results were achieved despite an aggressive inventory clearance
ahead of introduction of razors of next-generation, a new
triple-blade razor called Mach 3.
</P>
<P>
"We expect to have a very strong new products program this
year," Zeien said in a statement. "With more than 20 new products
scheduled for launch in 1998, we have significant potential to
expand our existing franchises." 
</P>
