<DOCNO> XIE19980417.0133 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ADB to Provide Information in Asian Languages </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 17 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank (ADB)
announced here Friday that it has approved a 450,000-U.S.-dollar
technical assistance grant for translating its documents from
English into some Asian languages.
</P>
<P>
In a statement released here, the bank said that the assistance
will help executing agencies better understand ADB's operational
documents, support the flow of information between the ADB and
non-governmental organizations, and foster their involvement in
the consultations, designing and implementation of ADB projects.
</P>
<P>
In the past, the bank said, difficulties have been encountered
in project processing and implementation by executing agencies due
to the unavailability of relevant bank documents in local
languages.
</P>
<P>
"The situation is particularly serious in the case of projects
where community involvement and participatory development are a
crucial element for successful implementation," it said.
</P>
<P>
English is the working language of the Manila-based bank.
</P>
<P>
The bank said that translations will be implemented initially
on a two-year pilot basis in Bangladesh, Cambodia, China,
Indonesia, Kazakstan and Vietnam.
</P>
<P>
Based on the pilot phase, the assistance may be expanded to
other ADB members, it said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
