<HEADLINE> Angola, Congo (K) to Tighten Industrial Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Angolan Industrial Minister
Maneul Duque held talks with the visiting Congo (K) industrial
Minister Babi Mbayi here Thursday, deciding to strengthen
industrial cooperation between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Duque said that after the meeting, the first contact between
the two countries for future industrial cooperation, a joint
technical group is to be set up to map out specific cooperation
plans, the State-run radio reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
Top on the agenda for cooperation, he said, are the building
of industrial management institutions, the construction of
industrial areas, the training of talents and some other
programs.
</P>
<P>
The two countries also planned to cooperate in the Southern
Africa Development Community (SADC) and the UN industrial
organization of which both countries are members.
</P>
<P>
Mbayi declared after the meeting that coordination meetings
would be held in turns in the two countries to discuss issues
concerning the cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Angola and Congo (K), two countries with long border line,
have enjoyed good relations. Angola offered Congo (K) great help
during the days when Laurent Kabila's forces tried to overthrow
former Zaire's President Mobuto Sese Seko, and Congo (K) in turn
has helped Angola in its peace process. 
</P>
