<HEADLINE> Stocks Continue Falling in Tokyo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Stock prices continued falling in
Tokyo Friday on speculative selling by foreign investors.
</P>
<P>
The Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected issues on the First
Section of the Tokyo Stock Exchange lost 179.97 points, or 1.13
percent from Thursday's close to 15,703.80.
</P>
<P>
The broader-based Tokyo Stock Price Index (TOPIX), covering all
First Section issues, dropped 4.90 points, or 0.40 percent to
1,212.44.
</P>
<P>
Volume on the First Section grew to an estimated 430 million
shares from Thursday's 400 million shares.
</P>
<P>
Nippon Steel was the day's most heavily traded issue.
</P>
<P>
Traders said speculative selling by foreign investors was
noticeable throughout the day, as they tried to push down the
Nikkei index to below the 15,517 support line, registered at the
April 3 close.
</P>
<P>
Of the 1,328 issues listed on the First Section, losers
outnumbered gainers 670 to 442, with 166 remaining unchanged.
</P>
