<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Czech Davis Cup captain Vladimir
Savrda stepped down from his pole after Czech was defeated by
Switzerland in the first round of the world group early this month.
</P>
<P>
Savrda, who took over the team in 1996 from Tomas Smid, was
criticized for his strategy against the underdog Swiss.
</P>
<P>
