<HEADLINE> Five Chinese Students Win World Cup Tour </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Five Chinese students have won a
trip to France to watch the soccer World Cup finals and get a feel
of the French culture, the French Embassy in China announced on
Friday.
</P>
<P>
Wang Zhe from Beijing and four others will arrive in France on
June 30 before watching the quarterfinals, semifinals and the
final of the biggest soccer tournament.
</P>
<P>
They will also take part in some cultural exchanges and visit
several French cities.
</P>
<P>
The five students were selected from 167 candidates through
verbal and written tests on their knowledge of French soccer and
culture, including a popular French sports trivia program.
</P>
<P>
These candidates, who are all French language students, were
already regional winners of special examinations in 40 cities
across China.
</P>
<P>
They are among 600 students from 120 countries and regions,
five from each, who will tour France in the "Go To France '98"
event organized by the French Foreign Ministry. 
</P>
