<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Mixed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange closed mixed on Friday.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality Composite Index eased 0.56 of a
point to 628.78 and the Industrial Index shed 3.74 points to
1,157.75.
</P>
<P>
However, the all main board Emas Index firmed 0.47 of a point
to 160.07 and the Second Board Index rose 2.54 points to 147.84.
</P>
<P>
Gainers outpaced losers by 491 to 207, while 120 were unchanged
and 96 others were untraded.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover rose to 192.305 million shares worth 436.002
million ringgit (115.957 million U.S. dollars) from 185.182
million shares worth 474.499 million ringgit (126.196 million
dollars) on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Mainboard turnover rose to 168.235 million shares valued at
405.129 million ringgit (107.747 million dollars) from 163.836
million shares worth 446.189 million ringgit (118..667 million
dollars) on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The second board turnover increased to 24.070 million shares
valued at 30.873 million ringgit (8.21 million dollars) from
Thursday's 21.346 million shares worth 28.310 million ringgit
(7.529 million dollars).
</P>
<P>
Off-market deals was higher at 2.543 million shares valued at
9.488 million ringgit (2.523 million dollars) from Thursday's
2.152 million shares worth 12.898 million ringgit (3.43 million
dollars).
</P>
<P>
On a sectoral basis, consumer products accounted for 9.490
million shares traded on the mainboard, industrial products 12.750
million shares, construction 18.773 million shares,
trading/services 44.018 million shares, infrastructure 815,000
shares, finance 28.623 million shares, hotels 284,000 shares,
properties 23.371 million shares, plantation 6.374 million shares,
mining 993,000 shares, trusts 117,000 shares, closed/fund 247,000
shares and loans 22.379 million shares. 
</P>
