<HEADLINE> China to Hold Second Investment, Trade Fair </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, April 17 (Xinhua) -- The 2nd China Investment and
Trade Fair will be held in Xiamen in east China's Fujian
Province on September 8-12, Deputy Governor Cao Degan told a news
conference here today.
</P>
<P>
The official, who is attending the ongoing 83rd Chinese Export
Commodities Trade Fair here, said that all the Chinese provinces,
municipalities and autonomous regions will present
government-designated projects to invite overseas investments and
some foreign trade projects.
</P>
<P>
Investment seminars will also be held in an attempt to
provide policy advices, the official said.
</P>
<P>
Some 6,200 overseas business people attended the first fair in
1997, and signed 1,670 contracts involving 6.2 billion
U.S. dollars, 4.63 billion of which came from overseas investors.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that China had approved 3,970 overseas-backed
ventures during the first quarter of this year, and used 8.59
billion U.S. dollars in real terms, a year-on-year increase of 9.7
percent. 
