<HEADLINE> Russian State Duma Turns Down Kiriyenko as PM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 17 (Xinhua) -- The nomination of Sergei Kiriyenko
as Russian prime minister on Friday failed to pass the second vote
at the State Duma, the lower house of Russian parliament.
</P>
<P>
The deputies voted 115 in favor, 271 against with 11
abstentions to reject the nomination by President Boris Yeltsin.
</P>
<P>
Kiriyenko did not pass the first round of vote in the State
Duma for the post of prime minister on April 10.
</P>
<P>
Under the country's constitution, the premier's nomination
needs 226 votes in favour from the 450-seat lower house to be
confirmed. 
</P>
