Sergei Kiriyenko told the State Duma (the lower house of
parliament) on Friday that his government's economic program
submitted to parliament last week has not changed.
</P>
<P>
According to Russian press, Kiriyenko addressed the plenary
session of the Duma before the deputies started the second round
of voting on his premiership.
</P>
<P>
Kiriyenko said the economic program had been updated in the
light of criticism and proposals made during consultations.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the implementation of the economic policy was in
the center of attention at the consultations, and the numerous
steps outlined in the programs have already been taken.
</P>
<P>
Kiriyenko told the deputies that a government ordinance on the
restructuring of debts incurred by factories was signed on April
13.
</P>
<P>
In the address, he also called on the government to continue
measures to stop organized crimes.
</P>
<P>
As for the territorial dispute with Japan, Kiriyenko said
Russia admits the existence of a territorial dispute with Japan
but is not going to give away its territories. 
