<HEADLINE> Bosnian Serb PM Advises Karadzic to Surrender Himself </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Bosnian Serb Prime Minister
Milorad Dodik said here Thursday that former Bosnian Serb leader
Radovan Karadzic should surrender himself to the war crimes
tribunal in The Hague, Netherlands.
</P>
<P>
Dodik made the remarks in response to widespread rumors here
about Karadzic's whereabout after a meeting with Pavle, archbishop
of the Orthodox Eastern Church in Serbia, the Vecernje Novosti
daily reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Bosnian Serb republic is incapable of either arresting
Karadzic or preventing him from being arrested, Dodik said, adding
that it is best for him to surrender himself to The Hague tribunal.
</P>
<P>
Karadzic, together with some others, has been indicted by The
Hague tribunal as a war crimes suspect held responsible for
genocide in more than three years of ethnic conflicts in
Bosnia-Hezergovina. 
</P>
