<HEADLINE> Mozambican and S. African Lawyers Tighten </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Lawyers from Mozambique and South
Africa gathered here Thursday to discuss the possibility of
strengthening ties and build up a lawyers' forum in the Southern
African region.
</P>
<P>
Representatives of the Mozambican Lawyers' League and the Law
Society of South Africa agreed to establish special commissions
in each other's country to find out better way for cross-border
cooperation among lawyers.
</P>
<P>
Carlos Cauio, official with the Mozambican Lawyers' League,
said that South Africans would increase their investment in
Mozambique after they have a better knowledge of the laws in the
country.
</P>
<P>
Cauio said that participants at the meeting promised to try
their best to establish a lawyers' forum among lawyers of the
Southern African Development Community.
</P>
<P>
Botswana, Lesotho, Malawi, Namibia, Tanzania, Swaziland,
Zimbabwe and Zambia have agreed to establish the regional
lawyers' forum. 
</P>
