<HEADLINE> Macao Airport Sea Terminal Expected to Be Started in May </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Construction of a new sea port terminal
that will offer express service from the Macao international Airport
to Hong Kong is expected to begin within a month, the Macao Daily
News reported on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted Stanley Ho, general manager of the Macao Tourism
and Amusement Company (STDM), which will be the major investor of the
project, as saying that the project is near its final approval stage
from the Macao Government, and is expected to be started as soon as in
May.
</P>
<P>
First proposed three years ago, the terminal project will bring
better accessibility to Hong Kong for those passengers using the
Macao Airport.
</P>
<P>
Ho said the project will be completed in ten months at a total
cost of 200 million patacas (about 25 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
Currently, airport passengers destined for Hong Kong must go
through a series of customs procedure both at the airport and the Hong
Kong-Macao sea terminal, which is about half an hour drive away from
the airport. 
</P>
