<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nepal, China Sign Minutes on Economic Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Nepal and China signed here
Friday the minutes of the 8th session of the Nepal-China
Inter-governmental Economic and Trade Committee.
</P>
<P>
Liu Shanzai, visiting Chinese Vice Minister for Foreign Trade
and Economic Cooperation, and Ram Binod Bhattarai, Secretary of
Nepal's Finance Ministry, signed the minutes on behalf of their
respective governments.
</P>
<P>
At the three-day session which began Wednesday, delegations of
the two countries discussed and agreed on various areas of
bilateral cooperation, which include joint venture investment,
trade and commerce, road and transport, sports, health,
telecommunication, tourism and civil aviation, and taxes and
duties, said a press released issued by the Finance Ministry of
Nepal.
</P>
<P>
It said that both sides expressed strong desire to further
promote bilateral trade. And for this, the opening of new
entry-exit points, removal of barriers for fairer trade and
initiation of measures to develop balanced trade between the two
countries have been discussed.
</P>
<P>
The committee agreed that there is a great potential for
joint-venture investment. And Chinese entrepreneurs accompanying
the delegation and their Nepalese counterparts have agreed to set
up a cement factory with an annual capacity of 250,000-300,000
metric tons, and signed a letter of intent on joint production of
agricultural machinery.
</P>
<P>
Besides, they have agreed to renovate and expand the Lumbini
Sugar Mill, diversify and expand Hetauda Textile Industry, set up
a construction company and build a tea processing factory, said
the press release.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese side also agreed to provide an additional grant
assistance of 30 million RMB yuan (about 4 million U.S. dollars)
to Nepal's sports facilities project and other projects to be
decided between the two sides, and to provide 400,000 RNB yuan
(about 50,000 dollars) to the Nepal-China Non-governmental
Cooperation Forum as a start-up fund, the press release said.
</P>
<P>
Similarly, an understanding has been reached between the two
sides to provide technical assistance to B.P. Koirala Memorial
Cancer Hospital now under construction with China's grant
assistance, and China has agreed to provide spare parts for the
maintenance of trolley buses in Nepal, the press release added.
</P>
<P>
Liu Shanzai told the press after the signing ceremony that both
sides described the session as a complete success.
</P>
<P>
He said he and his Nepalese counterparts have explored news
ways and means and new growth points for further promoting the
warm relations existing between the two countries, and economic
and trade ties in particular.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, when meeting with Liu Shanzai, Nepali Finance Minister
Ram Saran Mahat said increased bilateral trade, joint venture,
Chinese investment in Nepal and some other development projects
will be Nepal's areas of priority in the future.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government economic and trade delegation left here
Friday for a visit to India, and then to Sri Lanka, the Maldives
and Malaysia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
