<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Marxism to Be Like Evergreen: Say Scholars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 17 (Xinhua) -- The secretary of the Beijing
University Committee of the Communist Party of China, Ren Yanshen,
told a forum on Communism's past, present and future, that since
coming to China 80 years ago, Marxism has been proven to be a
scientific theory and will see even greater splendor in the next
millennium.
</P>
<P>
The forum marks the 80th anniversary of Communism in China and
it is considered a significant event here, according to Xu
Quanxin, a CPC Central Committee Party School researcher.
</P>
<P>
In 1918, Li Dazhao, then head of the Beijing University
Library, began research on Communism and started China's first
research group on Karl Marx's theory.
</P>
<P>
The university became a center of the CPC in its infancy in the
1920s, and many Chinese leaders, including Mao Zedong, worked or
studied there.
</P>
<P>
In 1840, China was humiliated when it lost the Opium War
against Britain, and subsequently many Western powers invaded the
country. "China was facing a serious crisis at that time, and a
group of progressive scholars decided to introduce Marxism from
Russia to save the nation," explains Xiao Chaoran, a historian at
Beijing University.
</P>
<P>
Scholars and statesmen had tried various methods, including
Anarchism, to regain national glory, but it was the October
Revolution in Russia in 1917 that gave them the greatest hope.
</P>
<P>
And Beijing University became the center of Marxism because its
president, Cai Yuanpei, pursued a policy of encouraging different
schools of thought, according to Shi Zhongquan, of the CPC Central
Committee's Party History Research Center.
</P>
<P>
Communism has been through ups and downs in China since then,
but has succeeded through self-improvement and will become
immortal, according to Bai Keming, deputy head of the CPC Central
Committee's Publicity Department. He says that Marxism has entered
a new stage of development because of Deng Xiaoping Theory, which
is known as "contemporary Marxism".
</P>
<P>
The theory as applied by the CPC will rejuvenate China, he
says, and a modernized China in the 21st century will further
prove the correctness of Marxism.
</P>
<P>
The Education Ministry has decided to push the study of Deng
Xiaoping Theory at all universities in China, and most
universities already have Deng Xiaoping Theory courses. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980417.0209 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> American Couple Collects Donations of Medical Books for China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 17 (Xinhua) -- An American couple has collected
donations of medical books and audio and visual materials worth
130 million U.S. dollars for China since 1981.
</P>
<P>
The 50th container of donated books was transported to Tianjin
earlier this month, bringing the total weight of donations he and
his wife have collected during the past 17 years up to 1,000 tons,
said Jordan M. Phillips today during an interview with Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
He said the donations include three million medical books and
numerous video tapes and films for medical education and
demonstrations.
</P>
<P>
More than 700 medical universities and colleges, research
institutes and hospitals in China have received those books and
materials, which are about the latest developments in medical
science and technology, said the 74-year-old U.S. physician.
</P>
<P>
Phillips and his wife, Mary, made their first trip to China in
1979. They found that medical libraries in the interior of China
were short of new medical books because of the destruction
during the Cultural Revolution from 1966 to 1976.
</P>
<P>
In 1981, the couple established a non-profit organization,
the Medical Books for China International, to ask for book
donations in the United States. They wrote letters to 1,200
medical libraries across their country, requesting extra books.
</P>
<P>
There was an immediate response and their room was piled high
with the donated books and materials.
</P>
<P>
They began to ship the donations to Tianjin with the help of
the China Ocean Shipping Corp. in 1984, and the books were
distributed all over China by an acceptance committee of the
Tianjin Medical University.
</P>
<P>
To date, seven centers have been established in Beijing,
Hengyang, Ji'an, Kunming, Urumqi, Xuzhou and Huhhot to distribute
the donated books to libraries across China.
</P>
<P>
Phillips and his wife have visited China 62 times. The Health
Ministry of China awarded Phillips a China Health Medal in 1991
for his contributions to medical developments in China.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese consul-general in Los Angeles, Feng Shusen, in 1996
delivered a medal to the couple engraved with the Chinese national
emblem and the characters "Chinese People's Old Friends." The
medal was awarded at a celebration of the 15th anniversary of the
founding of the Medical Books for China International.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980417.0210 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-17 </DATE_TIME>
