<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Portuguese Prime Minister Antonio
Guterres arrived in Macao at noon today for a three-day visit here
before leaving for China's inland areas for an official visit.
</P>
<P>
This is his first visit to Macao since he became Portuguese
Prime Minister in 1995. His entourage includes dozens of
businessmen and six cabinet ministers such as Foreign Minister
Jaime Gama, Economic Affairs Minister Pina Moura, Science and
Technology Minister Mariano Gago.
</P>
