<HEADLINE> Top Research Institute to Assist Pudong Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 17 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese Academy of Sciences
(CAS), China's top research body, will cooperate with the Pudong
new area in the high-tech and new-technology fields to assist the
development zone in its rapid development.
</P>
<P>
Today's People's Daily reported that, in an effort to promote
the development of the country's high-tech industries, the CAS
will establish branches of its profitable high-tech ventures in
Pudong.
</P>
<P>
According to an agreement reached by the two sides, the CAS
will receive preferential treatment in running high-tech ventures
in Pudong.
</P>
<P>
Pudong announced that computer, modern biology and
pharmaceuticals and new material ventures also will receive
preferential treatment.
</P>
<P>
Pudong has listed the high-tech information sector as its
priority task for the next three years. The industrial output
value of high-tech ventures is expected to account for at least 25
percent of all ventures in Pudong.
</P>
<P>
Pudong also invited 11 CAS academicians and famous overseas
scholars to be science advisers. 
