<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka to Establish Central Gem Emporium </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, April 17 (Xinhua) -- The Sri Lankan Gem and Jewelry
Authority (SLGJA) will set up a central gem emporium (CGE) in
Colombo, SLGJA sources said Friday.
</P>
<P>
The CGE, which will cost 100 million Rupees (1.6 million U.S.
dollars), will be a well-developed modern version of gem emporium
with a range of new facilities similar to the present Gem and
Jewelry Exchange in the capital city, the sources said, adding
that they hoped the emporium will be used to organize gold booths
there.
</P>
<P>
To boost the gem industry and help those involved in the
industry, a similar gem center was established in the country
early this year, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
Sri Lanka has earned 164.3 million U.S. dollars from gems,
jewelry and out-diamond exports during the last 11 months of last
year. 
