<HEADLINE> New Minister Vows to Strengthen Supervision </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 17 (Xinhua) -- China will strengthen the
supervision over administrative bodies and severely punish people
involved in corruption, said He Yong, the newly appointed Minister
of Supervision.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with People's Daily (overseas edition), the
58-year-old minister expressed his confidence to do a good job,
though "it is a hard nut," said He, who has devoted himself to
numerous tasks since the appointment, the paper reported today.
</P>
<P>
When talking about the work of supervision, he said that the
priority will go to fighting corruption, and more efforts will be
made to crack down on embezzlement and bribery cases involving
large sums.
</P>
<P>
Issues that to the public resentment will be settled as
soon as possible, he promised, and fewer burdens will be imposed
on farmers and businesses.
</P>
<P>
He said emphasis will be put on correcting malpractice in all
trades, and checks of extra budget funds will be strengthened.
</P>
<P>
The ministry will continue to supervise the work of state
administrative bodies, he said, and further standardize the
country's financial order and improve the system of open, equal
and honest competition.  
</P>
