<BODY>
<HEADLINE> NPC Vice-Chairman Meets Canadian Guests </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Tian Jiyun, vice chairman of the
Standing Committee of the National People's Congress (NPC), met
here today with Canadian visitors led by Diane Marleau, minister
for International Cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Tian told his visitors that the two countries enjoy good
cooperative relations, particularly in trade and economic
cooperation, environmental protection, poverty relief and
personnel training. The Canadian Ministry of International
Cooperation and Canadian International Development Agency (CIDA)
played a significant role in the regard, he added.
</P>
<P>
After briefing the visitors on the Chinese people's congress
system and its achievements in promoting democracy and the
introduction of a legal system, Tian said that China hopes to
further cooperation between the two countries, as well as between
the NPC and the Canadian parliament.
</P>
<P>
Tian believed that Marleau's China visit can enhance the
friendship between people of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Marleau said that the two countries have kept good ties in many
fields and the Canadian side expects to expand such cooperation in
the future, in which the two countries can learn from each other
and share useful experience.
</P>
<P>
She said that her ministry and the CIDA will continue their
efforts in furthering bilateral cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Marleau and her party are visiting China at the invitation of
Shi Guangsheng, minister of Foreign Trade and Economic
Cooperation.  
</P>
</TEXT>
