<HEADLINE> S. Africa to Launch Female Condom </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, April 17 (Xinhua) -- The South African
Department of Health said it would launch a female condom in June
this year.
</P>
<P>
The decision was made to offer women in the country the
opportunity to protect themselves from unplanned children and
sexually transmitted diseases.
</P>
<P>
However, the condom will not be made widely available until
the trial period indicates popular support, said the department
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Some clinics, including primary health care clinics, family
planning clinics and adolescent health services in both rural and
urban areas of several provinces, have been selected to monitor
the trial.
</P>
<P>
The United Nations Aids/HIV organization will be running a
workshop from April 20-22 in Pretoria, South Africa, to
informally consult representatives on launching and promoting the
female condom, the Health Department officials said. 
