<HEADLINE> Hughes Company Earns 54 Million Dollars in First Quarter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES, April 16 (Xinhua) -- Hughes Electronics Corp. of
the United States reported Thursday that it has earned 53.7
million U.S. dollars in the first quarter of this year.
</P>
<P>
The earnings was 23.9 million dollars in January-March period
last year, according to the figures released by the company.
</P>
<P>
The increase was attributed to the strong growth in the
business of DirecTV, which is a kind of direct-to-home broadcast
service, and improved satellite sales of Hughes company. 
</P>
</TEXT>
