<HEADLINE> Denmark to Support SADC Organ </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, April 17 (Xinhua) -- The Danish government has pledged
support for the Southern African Development Community (SADC)
organ for politics, defense and security and the region's efforts
to establish its own peacekeeping force.
</P>
<P>
Danish Ambassador to Zimbabwe Erik Fiil Thursday told The
Herald that Denmark was opening new areas of cooperation with all
SADC member states.
</P>
<P>
"To conclude such a project as part of our development
cooperation program would have been unthinkable only a few years
ago... but it is only recently after the international climate
has become conducive to establishment of regional initiatives in
this field, that a small country like Denmark can be of
assistance to these programs," said the ambassador.
</P>
<P>
He said peacekeeping and conflict prevention was needed for
sustainable economic and social development which his country
supported.
</P>
<P>
On cooperation with Zimbabwe, he said a private sector program
which involved twinning Zimbabwean and Danish private companies
was being introduced.  
</P>
