<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Circular Calls for Ensuring Light Industry Production Objectives </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 17 (Xinhua) -- The State Economic and Trade
Commission's Light Industry Bureau recently called on local light
industry departments to adopt effective measures to reverse
falling industrial production.
</P>
<P>
The bureau issued a circular recently, requiring local
departments to help realize the targeted eight growth in gross
domestic product (GDP).
</P>
<P>
Statistics for the first two months of this year show that the
industrial production value for China's light industry, which
includes the textile, tobacco and household electrical appliances
industries, hit 339.5 billion yuan, up 10.9 percent on the 1997
period, but nonetheless an increase rate much lower than expected.
</P>
<P>
The total January-February production value for enterprises
administered by the light industry bureau stood at 77.4 billion
yuan, down 0.5 percent on an annual basis.
</P>
<P>
Despite the upturn of production during March, the first
quarter growth figure is expected to hit a mere three percent.
</P>
<P>
The circular stressed that light industry production should
maintain a proper growth rate of at least eight percent, but
preferably 10 percent.
</P>
<P>
The industry must actively explore the domestic market and
accelerate adjustments to the product structure.
</P>
<P>
The circular also called for efforts to tap the vast potential
of rural areas, and to improve the channels enabling light
industrial products to enter the rural market.
</P>
<P>
Steady export growth should be maintained, according to the
circular, which also stressed that businesses should target South
America, the Commonwealth of Independent States, East Europe and
Africa as new potential markets.
</P>
<P>
Wu Jian'an, the Light Industry Bureau official in charge of
production plans, said that light industry administrative
departments should proceed with government restructuring plans and
strengthen economic management.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the bureau has dispatched four fact-finding
groups to coastal areas and central and western regions to gather
first-hand information which is expected to facilitate central
government decision-making.
</P>
<P>
The bureau will grant favorable policies and special assistance
to loss-making industries, such as the sugar, canned-food and
papermaking sectors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
