<HEADLINE> Beijing Increasing International Social Development Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Beijing is increasing its
international cooperation in ecology, environmental, public
health, disaster relief and prevention, and city planning and
management projects.
</P>
<P>
Recent statistics show that 49 percent of the city's cooperation
projects and over 90 percent of the international meetings held in
Beijing are related to the city's social development.
</P>
<P>
Zou Zuye, head of Beijing's Science and Technology Commission,
says that the capital will place greater priority on these
projects to help maintain economic growth.
</P>
<P>
He said that this will also involve urban construction and
administration.
</P>
<P>
So far, the city has cooperative relations with more than 80
countries and regions and has joined 36 international
organizations.
</P>
<P>
In urban communications, the city cooperated with France and
Britain in renovating part of its subway line from Fuxingmen
to Pingguoyuan.
</P>
<P>
In water resources, Beijing joined Britain in four projects,
one of which was monitoring the quality of water in the Miyun
Reservoir.
</P>
<P>
The city suffers from serious pollution problems and has been
starting more environmental protection projects with the help of
foreign countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
