<BODY>
<HEADLINE> AIDS Cases Increase Rapidly in Poland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WARSAW, April 16 (Xinhua) -- The number of people identified as
AIDS patients in Poland has reached 620, of whom 364 have died,
the national AIDS prevention bureau said.
</P>
<P>
Just in the first two months of this year, 114 new cases were
reported, bringing the number of AIDS cases from last year's 579
to 620, said A. Novak, an advisor on AIDS to the Department of
Health and Social Welfare minister.
</P>
<P>
According to the bureau, another 5,067 people in the country
are HIV positive.
</P>
<P>
The number of people with HIV, the virus which can lead to a
full-blown case of the AIDS disease, also has been rising rapidly
since 1985, when the country's first AIDS case was reported, said
Novak.
</P>
<P>
The advisor attributed the increase of AIDS cases and HIV
carriers to illegal drug use, saying that 65 percent of HIV
carriers in the country contracted the virus via drug use.
</P>
<P>
Currently there are 40,000 drug addicts in Poland. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
