<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka to Launch General Education Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka's General Education
Project (GEP) with World Bank assistance of 4.9 million U.S.
dollars is to be launched soon, a local newspaper reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
It aims to upgrade the quality of education in rural schools
and management and policy planning in the education sector under
the GEP, education ministry sources were quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
Restructuring the typical school environment and providing
sophisticated equipment for laboratories and libraries in all
rural schools is also on the agenda with a view to familiarizing
rural students with modern technology, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
In addition a further development of school curriculum as well
as upgrading of text books and education publications including
teachers guides will be done under the project.
</P>
<P>
The project will also back up and expand the education research
sector and map out an effective system of fund raising for the
education sector, the paper said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
