<HEADLINE> Thailand's Foreign Reserves Increase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Thailand's official foreign
reserves at the end of March were 27.7 billion U.S. dollars,
showing an increase of 900 million dollars from March 13,
according to the figures released by the Bank of Thailand
available Friday.
</P>
<P>
Under the restructuring plan negotiated with the International
Monetary Fund (IMF), Thailand must maintain official foreign
reserves of 23-25 billion dollars by the end of the year.
</P>
<P>
The increase in reserves should be attributed to the foreign
capital inflows.
</P>
<P>
In the last two weeks of March, the Bank of Thailand drew 300
million dollars in funds from the IMF rescue package, while
foreign capital inflow stood at 600 million dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
