<HEADLINE> Albania Signs Memo with IMF </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, April 16 (Xinhua) -- Albania and the International
Monetary Fund signed a memorandum of understanding on Wednesday
that will lead to greater cooperation between the two sides.
</P>
<P>
The Albanian Telegraphic Agency said the memo is designed to
pave way for the expected approval of a three-year bilateral
cooperative agreement named ESAF2. The ESAF2 is to be reviewed by
the IMF this May in Bonn, Germany.
</P>
<P>
The memo spelled out the macro-economic policy and economic
restructuring the Albanian government should carry out in the
first year of enacting ESAF2.
</P>
<P>
On October 7, 1997, Albanian Prime Minister Fatos Nano signed
a guarantee promising to satisfy all conditions set by the IMF and
other contributors in six months from the date of signature.
</P>
<P>
In consideration of the fact that Albania has delivered on its
promise, the IMF decided to sign ESAF2, a pact that would provide
hundreds of millions of U.S. dollars in aid in three years.
</P>
