<HEADLINE> People Injured In Beijing Train-Bus Collision In Stable Condition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 17 (Xinhua) -- The 14 people injured in
yesterday morning's train-bus collision here are in stable
condition, according to a doctor at Fengtai Hospital.
</P>
<P>
Three people were killed and four seriously injured at about
7:00 a.m. yesterday when a mini-bus carrying 17 people collided
with a locomotive at Wulidian near the Fengtai Railway Station on
the southwestern outskirts of the Chinese capital.
</P>
<P>
A preliminary investigation indicated that the cause of the
accident was the bus driver attempting to beat the oncoming train
to the road crossing.
</P>
<P>
The mini-bus was overturned and thrown to the side by the
violent impact, but trees at the side of the road prevented a
greater number of people from being killed, some experts believe.
</P>
<P>
All of the bus passengers were farmer-workers from Hebei
Province who were on their way to work. The injured people were
rushed to nearby Fengtai Hospital and the Beijing Emergency
Medical Center soon after the accident, and four are in serious
condition and one in critical condition.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing government and various departments were involved in
the operations after the accident. 
</P>
</TEXT>
