<HEADLINE> Guangzhou Residents Getting Travel Fever </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 17 (Xinhua) -- The number of Guangzhou
residents who last month registered to tour abroad has, for the
first time, surpassed that of domestic tourism, doubling the
figure reported at the same period of last year, the
Shanghai-based "Xinmin Evening News" reported.
</P>
<P>
The sharp rise is mainly attributed to deep price cuts on all
tourist routes abroad, which has hit a record low level in the
past decade, the paper reported.
</P>
<P>
Most travel routes are for Southeast Asian nations. The price
of touring Singapore, Malaysia and Thailand has dropped from 9,800
Hong Kong dollars to 6,000 and the price of touring Thailand also
dropped from 6,200 Hong Kong dollars to 3,000.
</P>
<P>
The number of travel agents in Guangdong Province has risen to
51 from two.  
</P>
