<HEADLINE> Chile, U.S. to Strengthen Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, April 16 (Xinhua) -- Chilean President Eduardo Frei
and visiting United States President Bill Clinton signed a joint
declaration on Thursday promising to further strengthen
cooperation between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
In the declaration, the presidents expressed satisfaction over
their healthy bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
They reaffirmed the commitment of their governments to achieve
a free trade agreement and to adopt concrete measures to promote
the competitiveness of their countries in the world economy.
