investment in October and to sign, as soon as possible, a final
agreement on the opening of skies so as to offer better air
transport services to facilitate trade contacts between peoples of
the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Also covered in the joint declaration are promise by the two
presidents to join efforts in fighting poverty and environmental
pollution.
</P>
<P>
As for the coming second summit of the Americas, to be held
April 18-19 in Santiago, Chile, they believed the summit will
contribute to strengthening hemispheric cooperation and promoting
development of the continent in a concrete and positive way.
</P>
<P>
During the two-day meeting, 34 heads of states were to discuss,
among other issues, a plan of action for implementation of the
Free Trade Area of the Americas (FTAA).
</P>
<P>
Clinton arrived here Thursday morning for a two-day visit
before taking part in the second summit of the Americas.
</P>
<P>
Accompanying the president is a high-level delegation formed by
Secretary of State Madeleine Albright, Attorney General Janet
Reno, Commerce Secretary William Daley and Education Secretary
Richard W. Riley. 
</P>
</TEXT>
