<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Swedish Parliament Approves Border Accord </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, April 16 (Xinhua) -- The Swedish parliament Thursday
approved the Schengen Accord, a border agreement in which member
states move towards scrapping their border controls between each
other.
</P>
<P>
The Schengen Accord was signed in Luxemburg in 1985 to achieve
free movement and promote free trade within the European Union
(EU).
</P>
<P>
The accord took effect in 1995 but so far only nine EU
countries have implemented it. These countries are Germany,
France, Netherlands, Belgium, Luxemburg, Italy, Austria, Portugal
and Spain.
</P>
<P>
Sweden, Denmark and Finland are to implement the accord by the
year 2000. 
</P>
</TEXT>
