<HEADLINE> Private Business Increasingly Important In Northern China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Private businesses have developed
rapidly in Tianjin, northern China's largest port city, and are
expected to play a more important role in local economic growth.
</P>
<P>
Tianjin had nearly 20,000 private companies by the end of last
year, employing 560,000 people.
</P>
<P>
Private businesses had 7.77 billion yuan in output value last
year, a 45 percent rise from 1996, and paid 670 million yuan in
taxes, 100 million yuan more than for 1996, accounting for 3.42
percent of the local total.
</P>
<P>
Tianjin has worked out regulations to increase the number of
private businesses and to help the sector expand and improve
production by providing preferential polices. 
