<HEADLINE> Uruguay Unemployment Hits Record Low </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO, April 16 (Xinhua) -- Uruguay's unemployment in
February was down to 10.1 percent, a record low for the past three
years, a report of the National Statistic Bureau said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Joblessness in the capital city of Montevideo dropped by the
biggest margin to 9.2 percent, the report said.
</P>
<P>
It attributed the better situation to various policies adopted
by the government to create jobs. These included encouraging
industrial and agricultural investment, promoting development of
the tourism industry and attracting direct foreign investment.
</P>
<P>
Uruguay's unemployment reached 13 percent in 1996 when the
government started to reform and readjust some state-owned
enterprises. 
</P>
