<HEADLINE> Exports Increasing in Tianjin Development Zone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, April 17 (Xinhua) -- The Tianjin Economic and
Technological Development Zone has exported 50,600 tons of goods
valued at 167 million U.S. dollars during the first three months
of this year.
</P>
<P>
This indicates an increase of 95 percent in volume and 26
percent in value over the same period of 1997.
</P>
<P>
The zone in the north China port city of Tianjin covers an area
of more than 70 square kilometers.
</P>
<P>
Sources from local Customs report that overseas-funded
enterprises in the zone have played the most important role in
exports. For the period, these companies exported 26,800 tons of
products which are processed in the zone with imported raw
materials. Their value was 138 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Motorola ranked first in the export growth rate, then
Samsung.
</P>
<P>
In addition, general trade exports have reached 20,400 tons,
valued at 12 million U.S. dollars, up 157 percent and 19 percent,
respectively.
</P>
<P>
The zone's products are mainly exported to North America,
European Union and East Asia.  
