<HEADLINE> Oil Output Increases in Argentina </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, April 16 (Xinhua) -- Argentina produced 48.4
million cubic meters of oil last year, an increase of 6.3 percent
over the previous year, a report said on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The annual report released by the Argentine Oil and Gas
Institute said production of gas reached 37 billion cubic meters,
7 percent up from 1996.
</P>
<P>
Almost 40 percent of the total crude output, or 19.3 million
cubic meters, was exported, the report added.
</P>
<P>
Argentina also exported 9.3 million cubic meters of oil and 1.1
million cubic meters of gas oil last year, an increase of 2.4 and
59 percent respectively over 1996..
</P>
<P>
The major customers of Argentine oil are Brazil, Chile and the
United States. 
