UNITED NATIONS -- In the right conditions, United Nations
peacekeeping operations can make the difference between peace and
war in Africa, UN Secretary-General Kofi Annan said on Thursday in
his report on Africa.
</P>
<P>
According to the UN Secretary-General, the UN peacekeeping
operations in Africa can play the roles as following: Separating
the protagonists and monitoring their conduct and Implementation
of comprehensive settlements, and in Africa, the Preventing
deployment and Protecting humanitarian interests. (Annan-UN
Roles-Africa)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- Full recovery in financially troubled Asia cannot
be achieved without Japan's efforts to pull its economy from
recession, warned U.S. Treasury Secretary Robert Rubin here on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
"Despite the welcome signs of stability now emerging (in
Asia)... we must guard against complacency," Rubin told the
Interim Committee, a policy-setting committee of the 182-nation
International Monetary Fund, which is holding its 50th meeting in
Washington.
</P>
<P>
Rubin said Japan, the world's second largest economy, accounts
for more than half of Asia's output. It "must generate substantial
growth to help maintain a growing world economy and to absorb a
growing share of imports from emerging markets." (US-IMF-Japan)
</P>
