<HEADLINE> Chelsea Fight Back to Reach Cup Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 16 (Reuters) - Chelsea reached the European Cup
Winner's Cup final for the first time since 1971 when they came
from behind to defeat Vicenza 3-1 in the second leg of their
semifinal for a 3-2 aggregate victory here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The winning goal came 14 minutes from time when veteran striker
Mark Hughes lashed home a left-foot volley just seven minutes
after coming on.
</P>
<P>
The Londoners, trailing 1-0 from the first leg after Vicenza,
once looked like out of the picture when Pasquale Luiso put
Vicenza a goal up after 32 minutes.
</P>
<P>
Chelsea levelled the scoreline three minutes later through
Uruguayan Gustavo Poyet and went ahead after 52 minutes when
player-coach Gianluca Vialli's pin-point cross found
fellow-Italian Zola who headed home from close range.
</P>
<P>
The Mark Hughes goal in the 76th minute clinched Chelsea their
place in the final against VfB Stuttgart in Stockholm on May
13. 
</P>
</TEXT>
