<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Increase of Drug Abuse in Moldova </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, April 16 (Xinhua) -- At least 27 tons of opium poppy
circulates illegally every year in the Republic of Moldova, of
which only 10 percent is confiscated by the police, according to
sources of the Moldovan Interior Ministry.
</P>
<P>
Tudor Sabii, chief of the Judiciary Police Direction within the
ministry, said that 1,769 persons in Moldova have been found using
opium poppy.
</P>
<P>
Since the beginning of this year, the police confiscated
132,546 kg of opium poppy and 225 kg of opium extract, which are,
according to Sabii, not an important quantity.
</P>
<P>
According to the same source, some 80 percent of the drug
abusers are between 15 and 34 years old, and 70 percent of them
are out of work. A total of 209 crimes influenced by drug abuse
have been registered since the beginning of this year.
</P>
<P>
Alexandru Maleev, chairman of the Drug Free Foundation,
considered that the total number of drug abusers in Moldova
outruns 170,000. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
