to a new high, fell 5.02 to 1,858.24.
</P>
<P>
The Russell 2000 index of smaller companies fell 2.70 to
484.42, and the American Stock Exchange composite index fell 3.11
to 739.35.
</P>
<P>
Merck, which slid more than 3 percent, reported a 14 percent
improvement in first-quarter profits, but the results were still
shy of Wall Street forecasts.
</P>
<P>
The dollar rose sharply against the Japanese yen today, sending
Tokyo stocks to losses by 2.5 percent.  
