<HEADLINE> U.S. Dollar Rises Overall </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, April 16 (Xinhua) -- The U.S. dollar rose sharply
against the Japanese currency Thursday, which pushed the dollar
higher against the German mark and most other major currencies.
</P>
<P>
In late New York trading, the dollar was quoted at 1.8057
marks, up from 1.7979 late Wednesday. The U.S. currency also
changed hands at 131.79 yen, up from 129.36 yen.
</P>
<P>
Finance officials of the major industrial nations met in
Washington Wednesday and Thursday, largely discussing the Asian
financial crisis and Japan's ailing economy in particular. They
urged Japan to produce more forceful plans that convince
international markets or authorities about its ability to revive
the economy, but failed to offer concrete help.
</P>
<P>
However, Japan did intervene aggressively in foreign exchange
markets last week in support of the yen.
</P>
<P>
Other late dollar rates in New York, compared with late
Wednesday: 1.5033 Swiss francs, up from 1.4928; 6.0515 French
francs, up from 6.0385; 1,783.00 Italian lire, up from 1,782.00;
and 1.4333 Canadian dollars, down from 1.4395.
</P>
<P>
The British pound was quoted at 1.6909 U.S. dollars, up from
1.6852 U.S. dollars Wednesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
