<HEADLINE> German Foreign Minister Criticizes Belgrade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, April 16 (Xinhua) -- German Foreign Minister Klaus Kinkel
on Thursday criticized Belgrade's continued resistance to foreign
intervention in the Kosovo conflict and threatened new sanctions
against Belgrade.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with the German radio Deutschlandfunk, Kinkel
said Belgrade's decision to hold a referendum on the issue of
foreign participation in a political dialogue over the future
status of Kosovo was "a step in the wrong direction and a new
obstacle to the end of the conflicts".
</P>
<P>
Kinkel also warned that the international contact group could
move to impose new punitive measures on Belgrade if their demands
were not met.
</P>
<P>
Separately, Ljubisa Ristic, who chairs the foreign committee of
the Yugoslav parliament, said in Bonn on Thursday that a foreign
part in the solution of Kosovo conflict would be only acceptable
when Yugoslavia was admitted back into international
organizations.
</P>
<P>
Ristic expressed Belgrade's hope to join the Council of Europe.
</P>
</TEXT>
