<HEADLINE> Gold Mine Found in Northern Greece </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, April 16 (Xinhua) -- Greece's "Silver Ore" Barytes Ltd.
announced here Thursday that the Thracian gold mining company had
located gold deposits in an area of 700 meters long and 100 to 300
meters wide in the northern part of the country.
</P>
<P>
The results of drilling for gold in southern Perama and Perama
Dasaki were also encouraging, said Silver Ore, Greece's biggest
mining company and one of the strongest in Europe.
</P>
<P>
Silver Ore has a 33.3 percent interest in Thracian Gold Mining
Ltd., while the French company La Source has a 44.5 percent
holding and the Canadian firm Inmet Mining corporation a 22.2
percent.
</P>
<P>
In ancient times, Greece was a major gold producer with mines
centered mainly in Macedonia, but there has been very little
activity in recent decades. 
</P>
</TEXT>
