<HEADLINE> Tanzanian President Back From China Tour </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, April 16 (Xinhua) -- Tanzanian President
Benjamin returned to his country Thursday evening after ending a
six-day state visit to cement ties with China.
</P>
<P>
Mkapa was received at the Dar es Salaam airport by
Vice-President Omar Ali Juma and Chief of Tanzanian People's
Defense Force Gen. Robert Mboma.
</P>
<P>
During his tour to China from April 8 to 13, Mkapa held talks
with Chinese President Jiang Zemin, Prime Minister Zhu Rongji and
other state leaders.
</P>
<P>
Talking about the visit, Mkapa said briefly, "It's very good."
</P>
<P>
Tanzanian trade officials said Mkapa had reached agreement
with Jiang on several projects that need to be implemented in
Tanzania.
</P>
<P>
The Tanzanian President, accompanied by his wife Anna, and
Minister of Foreign Affairs and International Cooperation Jakaya
Mrisho Kikwete, visited Beijing, Hunan Province, Shanghai and
Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Mkapa came back en route to Dubai of the United Arab Emirates,
where he had a working visit.
</P>
<P>
Asked about his impression on China, the foreign minister
said, "It's a great country... It's encouraging, inspiring...
</P>
<P>
"China is doing tremendously well," Kikwete said. "The country
is achieving all-round development."
</P>
<P>
"Practical changes are taking place," he added.
</P>
<P>
Kikwete also said Shanghai is spectacular, where he had
visited free trade zones and agricultural projects.
"Nothing is impossible," the foreign minister concluded. 
</P>
</TEXT>
