<DOCNO> XIE19980417.0323 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Irish Parliament to debate Ulster Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 16 (Xinhua) -- The Irish government announced
Thursday that the country's parliament will hold a special debate
next week to decide whether to hold a referendum on May 22 on the
Northern Ireland peace agreement reached last week.
</P>
<P>
An Irish government spokeswoman was quoted by press reports
from Dublin as saying that the parliament will also debate next
Tuesday and Wednesday whether to approve a motion, signed by the
country's six main parties, to endorse the peace deal.
</P>
<P>
Under the peace agreement, Northern Ireland will remain within
British control while building closer links with the Republic of
Ireland.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the deal proposes that Ireland should drop its
constitutional claim to Northern Ireland. A referendum on the deal
will be held simultaneously in Ireland and Northern Ireland on May
22.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
