<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Moldova: Misappropriation, Main Cause of Crimes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, April 16 (Xinhua) -- Some 80 percent of all grave
crimes in the Republic of Moldova are committed for the purpose of
misappropriation, the Moldovan news agency BASA-PRESS quoted a
report of the Interior Ministry as saying.
</P>
<P>
During the first quarter of this year, the state and the
population have lost more than 29 million Moldovan lei (6.17
million U.S. dollars), of which only 1.31 million lei (278,723.4
dollars) was recovered by the police.
</P>
<P>
The report also said that 60 percent of crimes and offenses
registered by the police are thefts from private property, in
particular from apartments. According to statistics, individuals
lost in thefts since the beginning of this year at least 11.5
million lei (2.45 million dollars). As compared with the same
period of 1997 this sum was 4.5 million lei (957,446.8 dollars).
</P>
<P>
Many criminal groups in Moldova are specialized in car theft on
order, according to Andrei Vataman, deputy chief of the criminal
police direction at the Interior Ministry.
</P>
<P>
The rate of discovery is too low, the police complain, only 24
percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
